<http://identifiers.org/rgd/1565556>
        a       owl:Class .

gomodel:SYNGO_755  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Authors used a polyclonal antibody against AIDA-1 generated in rabbit to study the protein distribution in vivo. This antibody identifies at least different isoforms of AIDA-1 (AIDA-1d, AIDA-1e and EB-1), being AIDA-1d and 1e found in synaptosomes and PSD fractions. Immunogold EM performed in hippocampus and more precisely in CA1 stratum radiatum shows gold particles closely associated with the PSD. Analysis of the location of those particles reveals a mean distance of 13 +/- 2 nm from the postsynaptic plasma membrane.\n\n14/6/2017 Pim\n- Literal: \"AIDA-1 is distributed fairly uniformly along the PSD, decreasing rapidly at its edge\". Experimental description: Experiments were carried out on 13 adult male Sprague-Dawley rats ranging from 3 to 10 months old, from Charles River Laboratories (Raleigh, NC). Four were used for diaminobenzidine (DAB) staining, four were used for confocal microscopy, two were used for preembed- ding electron microscopy, and three were used for post- embedding electron microscopy." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0575-6950" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1585-539X" ;
        dc:date           "2017-08-10" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_755" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

